description:
Service Usage

A Party is any person or organisation that directly or indirectly interacts with DIACs core business. A Partys interaction with DIAC is defined by one or many different Roles e.g. a Person can have the role of Applicant, Sponsor or Agent. An Organisation can have roles including Agency and Sponsor.

Service Usage

A Party is any person or organisation that directly or indirectly interacts with DIACs core business. A Partys interaction with DIAC is defined by one or many different Roles e.g. a Person can have the role of Applicant, Sponsor or Agent. An Organisation can have roles including Agency and Sponsor.
By design, Party information will be consolidated in the Client Data Hub (CDH) to support the 360 degree view of Party; SV325 service will allow consumers to retrieve partys basic level of consolidated client information. This information will include:
Party Details
Names and Aliases
Identifiers
Personal or Organizational data
Party of interest Indicator

Service Behaviour

This service retrieves a consolidated collection of basic data relating to a specific Party stored within the CDH, identified using a valid System Identifier for the request.

Service Variants

SV288 Retrieve Consolidated Party Identifiers, SV277 Retrieve Consolidated Party Details.

Service Dependencies

This service relies on the consumer providing a valid unique System Identifiers, for example CDH Party Id; PID; SCID; or CID.

Service Composition

This is not a composite service

Service Flow

Service Flow
An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the Retrieve Consolidated Party Name Summary service on the ESB;
ESB transforms the incoming request message RetrieveConsolidatedPartyNameSummaryRequest to TCRMService as per SV325v01.00Micro.xls and send the message to CDH
CDH executes the TCRMService and returns an XML message TCRMService to ESB.
ESB receives TCRMService message and transforms it to RetrieveConsolidatedPartyNameSummaryResponse
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the CDH provider returns an error.
ESB transforms Error into Enterprise Error Message as per section Error! Reference source not found..
ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload.
Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
If the service call was timeout, ESB should return error as per section Error! Reference source not found. to the consumer.

Transformation

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required
